WEBVTT

00:00.735 --> 00:02.201
I can't do this.

00:02.203 --> 00:03.302
You're the biggest bitch
I know.

00:03.304 --> 00:04.703
Don't tell me
you can't do this.

00:04.705 --> 00:05.971
Man:<i> This has been</i>
<i> the defining moment</i>

00:05.973 --> 00:06.972
<i> Of mellie grant's</i>
<i> political career,</i>

00:06.974 --> 00:08.307
<i> Previously on "scandal"...</i>

00:08.309 --> 00:09.641
I've underestimated you,
I think, gabby.

00:09.643 --> 00:11.377
You owe me an apology

00:11.379 --> 00:12.778
For not bothering
to learn my name.

00:12.780 --> 00:14.346
When you told me
fitz loved me,

00:14.348 --> 00:15.481
What you really meant

00:15.483 --> 00:17.182
I was supposed to
choose you.

00:17.184 --> 00:18.117
Huck:
You are nobody's father.

00:18.119 --> 00:19.852
-You were right.
-Welcome home, son.

00:19.854 --> 00:22.221
You have the oval.

00:22.223 --> 00:23.489
This is
what power looks like.

00:23.491 --> 00:25.057
Guess what --
I am a big dog.

00:25.059 --> 00:26.959
Fitz:
I was trying to save us!

00:26.961 --> 00:28.460
There is no us!

00:28.462 --> 00:29.495
We tried.

00:29.497 --> 00:31.063
We did.

00:33.667 --> 00:37.069
Announcer: "the liberty report"
with sally langston.

00:37.071 --> 00:39.705
Lovers of liberty,
we are back.

00:39.707 --> 00:41.707
Now, where were we?

00:41.709 --> 00:44.410
Ah, power.

00:44.412 --> 00:46.345
Power, my dear lovers
of liberty,

00:46.347 --> 00:48.514
Is the beating heart
of our nation's bosom.

00:48.516 --> 00:51.884
The high and mighty members of
the political elite feed on it,

00:51.886 --> 00:54.086
Breed on it,
for power is the host,

00:54.088 --> 00:57.823
The enormous teat off which
this entire town suckles.

00:57.825 --> 00:59.258
Oh, and you wonder why

00:59.260 --> 01:00.826
Washington can't get
anything done.

01:00.828 --> 01:03.162
The hunt for power
is all-consuming.

01:03.164 --> 01:05.731
Everyone always needs more,
and nobody ever has enough.

01:05.733 --> 01:07.599
The stories I could tell you.

01:10.037 --> 01:11.103
Thank you.

01:21.882 --> 01:23.882
[ chuckles ]

01:23.884 --> 01:25.517
Celebrity.

01:25.519 --> 01:28.854
Has your, uh, newfound notoriety
been good for business?

01:28.856 --> 01:30.789
Please don't start.

01:30.791 --> 01:31.890
Olivia,
you're overcompensating.

01:31.892 --> 01:33.192
You're starting.

01:33.194 --> 01:34.593
You stood
on the mountaintop.

01:34.595 --> 01:37.029
The ring of fire
was around you.

01:37.031 --> 01:38.630
You played him
like a fiddle.

01:38.632 --> 01:40.232
You held power
in your hands.

01:40.234 --> 01:41.800
You<i> were</i> power.

01:41.802 --> 01:44.269
You had the oval.

01:44.271 --> 01:46.972
My baby had the oval.

01:46.974 --> 01:50.976
You were running the place,
and he was clueless.

01:50.978 --> 01:52.544
Tell me I'm wrong.

01:54.815 --> 01:56.482
It's better this way.

01:56.484 --> 01:57.950
No.

01:57.952 --> 01:59.785
You can fool those twits
over there,

01:59.787 --> 02:01.053
But you can't fool me.

02:01.055 --> 02:03.222
Mnh-mnh.
You've tasted blood.

02:03.224 --> 02:04.923
You know what it's like.

02:04.925 --> 02:07.292
You want it.

02:11.098 --> 02:13.632
He tried to make me
into a first lady.

02:13.634 --> 02:15.167
Hmm.

02:15.169 --> 02:17.336
It felt like I was some kind
of prisoner.

02:20.441 --> 02:22.908
Go ahead. Say it.

02:22.910 --> 02:24.476
Say what?

02:24.478 --> 02:26.478
That no one can ever cage me
unless I let them,

02:26.480 --> 02:29.181
That I was in control
all along

02:29.183 --> 02:31.817
Because true power
is never lost.

02:31.819 --> 02:33.919
Freedom is in<i> my</i> hands.

02:33.921 --> 02:34.786
Say it.

02:34.788 --> 02:36.155
[ chuckles ]

02:36.157 --> 02:37.456
Clearly I don't have to.

02:37.458 --> 02:39.591
[ scoffs ]

02:39.593 --> 02:41.760
I miss you.

02:41.762 --> 02:43.695
I wish you'd come by the house
more often.

02:43.697 --> 02:44.663
You know I can't do that.

02:44.665 --> 02:45.631
Because of him?

02:45.633 --> 02:47.099
Why is jake there?

02:47.101 --> 02:48.800
What is he doing there
with you?

02:48.802 --> 02:49.935
He hates you.

02:49.937 --> 02:51.703
Jake has come home.

02:51.705 --> 02:53.605
So should you.

02:53.607 --> 02:56.608
Then again, perhaps it is better
to fight for the pleasure

02:56.610 --> 02:59.444
Of ripping the beating heart
of power from america's chest,

02:59.446 --> 03:01.313
To hold it in your bloody hands,

03:01.315 --> 03:03.949
Than it is to never have entered
the battle at all.

03:03.951 --> 03:06.618
After all, to be empty-handed
is to be powerless.

03:06.620 --> 03:08.987
And in this town,
powerless means impotent.

03:08.989 --> 03:12.057
And who wants to be impotent?

03:16.964 --> 03:18.664
You're late.

03:18.666 --> 03:20.399
You knew I was at dinner
with my father.

03:20.401 --> 03:21.366
I don't like waiting.

03:21.368 --> 03:23.202
Then<i> don't.</i> Leave.

03:23.204 --> 03:25.437
You really want me to go?

03:29.543 --> 03:32.344
[ otis redding's & carla thomas'
"tramp" plays ]

03:32.346 --> 03:34.246
[ sighs ]

03:39.220 --> 03:40.919
Carla: Tramp.

03:40.921 --> 03:42.221
Otis:
What you call me?

03:42.223 --> 03:43.522
Tramp.
You didn't.

03:43.524 --> 03:46.725
You don't wear continental
clothes or stetson hats.

03:46.727 --> 03:49.328
Well, I'll tell you
one dog-gone thing.

03:49.330 --> 03:51.496
It makes me feel good
to know one thing.

03:51.498 --> 03:54.900
♪ I know I'm a lover ♪

03:54.902 --> 03:57.069
Matter of opinion.

03:57.071 --> 03:58.270
That's all right.

03:58.272 --> 04:00.973
Mama was. Papa, too.

04:04.878 --> 04:08.914
♪ and I'm the only child ♪

04:08.916 --> 04:12.117
♪ lovin' is all I do ♪

04:14.188 --> 04:15.554
You know what, otis?

04:15.556 --> 04:16.788
What?

04:16.790 --> 04:17.723
You're country.

04:17.725 --> 04:19.191
That's all right.

04:19.193 --> 04:20.626
You straight
from the georgia woods.

04:20.628 --> 04:22.027
That's good.

04:22.029 --> 04:23.729
You know what?

04:23.731 --> 04:27.599
You wear overalls
and big, old brogan shoes,

04:27.601 --> 04:29.568
And you need a haircut,
tramp.

04:29.570 --> 04:31.970
Haircut?
Woman, you foolin'.

04:31.972 --> 04:34.840
♪ ooh, I'm a lover ♪

04:37.544 --> 04:39.878
Mama was.
Grandmama too.

04:39.880 --> 04:41.413
Papa too.

04:41.415 --> 04:42.714
Don't make you one.

04:45.219 --> 04:50.055
♪ but I'm the only
son of a gun ♪

04:50.057 --> 04:52.658
♪ this side of the sun ♪

04:52.660 --> 04:55.227
[ both breathing heavily ]

04:55.229 --> 04:58.163
♪♪

04:58.165 --> 05:00.432
Tramp!

05:00.434 --> 05:01.967
That's right.

05:11.478 --> 05:14.446
You know what, otis?
I don't care what you say.

05:14.448 --> 05:16.581
You're still a tramp.
Ah, sweet washington.

05:16.583 --> 05:19.518
The lines people will cross
to get just a bit of power here.

05:19.520 --> 05:21.086
The scheming, the planning,

05:21.088 --> 05:23.355
The favors bought and sold
and stolen --

05:23.357 --> 05:27.959
Why, it's true modern warfare --
a bloody, bloody battle.

05:27.961 --> 05:30.262
No one emerges unscathed.

05:30.264 --> 05:32.831
I couldn't be prouder
to be an american.

05:32.833 --> 05:34.333
How about you?

05:43.310 --> 05:45.410
[ cellphone rings, beeps ]

05:47.381 --> 05:49.381
Good evening, mr. President.

05:49.383 --> 05:51.149
Hey, abby. You busy?

05:51.151 --> 05:54.152
At [scoffs]
2:00 in the morning?

05:54.154 --> 05:55.954
No, sir. I'm free.
What's up?

05:55.956 --> 05:58.523
I'm gonna need my schedule
cleared for the next three days

05:58.525 --> 06:00.225
So I can prepare
for the east asia summit.

06:00.227 --> 06:01.460
Okay.

06:01.462 --> 06:02.627
You have it?

06:02.629 --> 06:03.662
Do I have...?

06:03.664 --> 06:04.696
My schedule.

06:04.698 --> 06:07.699
Oh, sir, I-I do,

06:07.701 --> 06:12.237
But, uh...You would probably
be more, uh, efficient

06:12.239 --> 06:15.073
If you talk to cyrus
about your schedule.

06:15.075 --> 06:16.575
You know, him being
chief of staff and all.

06:16.577 --> 06:17.542
I'm on the phone with you
right now.

06:17.544 --> 06:18.643
How is that not efficient?

06:18.645 --> 06:21.213
[ sighs ]
you're absolutely right, sir.

06:21.215 --> 06:23.148
Let's see.

06:23.150 --> 06:24.483
I can clear up most
of your schedule,

06:24.485 --> 06:27.319
But I can't get you out
of the gridiron dinner.

06:27.321 --> 06:28.820
You should join me
for that.

06:28.822 --> 06:30.655
I'd rather not.

06:30.657 --> 06:31.523
It'll be fun.

06:31.525 --> 06:32.657
No, it won't.

06:32.659 --> 06:34.693
No, but we can talk
about the summit.

06:34.695 --> 06:37.028
I can't go, sir.

06:37.030 --> 06:37.863
Why not?

06:37.865 --> 06:40.399
It's leo.

06:40.401 --> 06:41.400
Leo?

06:41.402 --> 06:43.435
Well, he's sick --
very sick.

06:43.437 --> 06:45.370
Terrible flu.

06:45.372 --> 06:48.607
He's here right next to me,
trying to sleep.

06:48.609 --> 06:50.108
I'll have charlotte send over
some chicken soup

06:50.110 --> 06:51.243
From this place I know
in bethesda tomorrow.

06:51.245 --> 06:52.077
He'll love it.

06:52.079 --> 06:54.513
Very kind of you, sir.

06:54.515 --> 06:56.681
Not a problem.

06:56.683 --> 06:58.517
So, let's talk about
this carbon-emissions cap

06:58.519 --> 07:00.051
We want president guo
to agree to.

07:00.053 --> 07:01.386
There another room
you can go in?

07:01.388 --> 07:03.255
You should probably let leo
get his rest.

07:03.257 --> 07:06.091
Of course, sir. Moving to
another room right now.

07:06.093 --> 07:08.593
[ door opens ]

07:08.595 --> 07:11.897
Hey, we got a client.
Are you gonna open the door?

07:11.899 --> 07:14.299
I'm in my pajamas.
What do you need, huck?

07:14.301 --> 07:15.534
Uh, we got a client.

07:15.536 --> 07:16.535
You could've called.

07:16.537 --> 07:18.236
This isn't the kind
of client

07:18.238 --> 07:20.038
You want to talk about
on the phone,

07:20.040 --> 07:22.374
Given the usual nsa phone
surveillance that goes on.

07:22.376 --> 07:24.242
Are you gonna open the door?
Are you okay?

07:24.244 --> 07:25.544
I'm fine.
What do you mean?

07:25.546 --> 07:27.312
I mean, you won't open the door,
and that's weird.

07:27.314 --> 07:28.413
Is there someone in there?

07:28.415 --> 07:29.981
What do you mean
about the client?

07:29.983 --> 07:32.117
"this isn't the kind of client
you want to talk about

07:32.119 --> 07:33.885
On the phone,
because of nsa surveillance."

07:33.887 --> 07:35.487
Oh, yeah, we definitely
do not want

07:35.489 --> 07:36.888
Anyone at the nsa
to hear about this.

07:36.890 --> 07:39.090
Why?
Who's the client?

07:39.092 --> 07:40.525
The head of the nsa.

07:45.632 --> 07:47.799
Get out. Now.

07:47.801 --> 07:50.469
Quinn: Air force lieutenant
general diane peters --

07:50.471 --> 07:52.838
Director of the national
security agency,

07:52.840 --> 07:55.006
Chief of the central
security service,

07:55.008 --> 07:56.508
Commander of u.S. Cyber command.

07:56.510 --> 07:57.909
Say that five times fast.

07:57.911 --> 07:59.811
Graduated from
the air force academy

07:59.813 --> 08:01.980
With a double major
in computer science

08:01.982 --> 08:03.448
And electrical engineering.

08:03.450 --> 08:05.450
Awarded the air force
distinguished service medal

08:05.452 --> 08:07.452
For the safe extraction
of a nato unit

08:07.454 --> 08:09.454
Pinned down behind
enemy lines in sarajevo.

08:09.456 --> 08:11.790
She ran the threat operation
center until three years ago

08:11.792 --> 08:13.992
When president grant appointed
her director of the nsa.

08:13.994 --> 08:15.527
First woman to hold that post.

08:15.529 --> 08:17.162
She's a total badass.

08:17.164 --> 08:20.131
I was gonna say trailblazer,
but, yeah, badass works, too.

08:20.133 --> 08:22.601
Yeah, but how does the badass
head of a spy agency

08:22.603 --> 08:24.269
Fall victim
to a computer virus?

08:24.271 --> 08:25.971
Wasn't really a virus.
It was a rootkit.

08:25.973 --> 08:27.272
A rootkit?

08:27.274 --> 08:28.874
A program
that allows a hacker

08:28.876 --> 08:30.942
To take control of a computer
and open any program they want.

08:30.944 --> 08:32.878
This is the surveillance feed
of my home office,

08:32.880 --> 08:36.314
And that -- that was my
desktop computer an hour ago.

08:36.316 --> 08:37.949
Watch.

08:37.951 --> 08:39.985
The computer starts copying
files all by itself.

08:39.987 --> 08:41.553
By the time I saw
what was happening,

08:41.555 --> 08:43.455
They'd already copied hundreds
of documents.

08:43.457 --> 08:45.056
Which file were
they looking for?

08:45.058 --> 08:47.659
The code name
was project mercury.

08:47.661 --> 08:48.994
That's really
all I can say.

08:48.996 --> 08:50.662
It's classified at
the very highest level.

08:50.664 --> 08:52.631
The nsa is listening to
our leaders' phone calls,

08:52.633 --> 08:54.332
Reading their e-mails,
their text messages.

08:54.334 --> 08:55.467
How do you know
about project mercury?

08:55.469 --> 08:56.835
It's all over the darknet.

08:56.837 --> 08:59.137
Kind of assumed it was another
crackpot conspiracy,

08:59.139 --> 09:00.839
But cool to know
it's actually true.

09:00.841 --> 09:02.507
This information
cannot get out.

09:02.509 --> 09:04.242
And I take it those aren't
personal files,

09:04.244 --> 09:05.911
And it's against
agency rules

09:05.913 --> 09:07.913
To keep work files
on your home computer,

09:07.915 --> 09:09.381
Although
lots of people do it.

09:09.383 --> 09:10.649
There's no way that program

09:10.651 --> 09:12.684
Could've gotten past
my cyber security system.

09:12.686 --> 09:13.752
I designed it myself.

09:13.754 --> 09:15.353
It's state-of-the-art
and impenetrable.

09:15.355 --> 09:17.022
Diane's right.
Her system's airtight.

09:17.024 --> 09:18.757
So how did they gain access
to her computer?

09:18.759 --> 09:20.492
Well, the trojan
that delivered the rootkit

09:20.494 --> 09:22.193
Was installed directly
into her home server,

09:22.195 --> 09:23.328
Probably via thumb drive.

09:23.330 --> 09:24.729
So the hack came from inside
the house.

09:24.731 --> 09:26.364
Spooky.

09:26.366 --> 09:28.533
Has anyone been
in this house recently?

09:28.535 --> 09:30.936
William torrance -- project
developer for sequoia moon --

09:30.938 --> 09:32.337
One of the biggest
and richest

09:32.339 --> 09:34.239
Mobile-app developers
on the planet.

09:34.241 --> 09:36.174
Met diane at a conference
late last year.

09:36.176 --> 09:38.043
A few weeks ago, she officially
registered him

09:38.045 --> 09:39.544
As her significant other
with the nsa.

09:39.546 --> 09:41.379
Apparently,
things are getting serious.

09:41.381 --> 09:43.548
It wasn't billy.
It couldn't have been.

09:43.550 --> 09:46.418
I know this is difficult,
but, diane, he is a programmer.

09:46.420 --> 09:49.087
It's my job to know
people's secrets,

09:49.089 --> 09:50.522
Assess threats,
predict behavior.

09:50.524 --> 09:52.057
No one else
was in that house?

09:52.059 --> 09:53.525
There's no sign
of forcible entry,

09:53.527 --> 09:55.093
And her alarm
company confirmed

09:55.095 --> 09:56.761
Her system
wasn't tampered with.

09:56.763 --> 09:58.930
Meanwhile, billy's cell has been
shut off for 18 hours.

09:58.932 --> 10:00.565
Read the signs.

10:00.567 --> 10:03.802
He's been in your house.
He had access to your server.

10:03.804 --> 10:05.036
He hasn't shown up for work.

10:05.038 --> 10:06.404
He's not answering
his cellphone.

10:06.406 --> 10:07.939
Have you ever dated
an engineer?

10:07.941 --> 10:10.075
They start writing
a new piece of code,

10:10.077 --> 10:11.476
And they become obsessed.

10:11.478 --> 10:13.478
Billy calls it
"getting in the zone."

10:13.480 --> 10:16.047
He drops off the grid all
the time, sometimes for days.

10:17.618 --> 10:18.717
I vetted him.

10:18.719 --> 10:20.452
I used every tool
at my disposal,

10:20.454 --> 10:22.487
And that includes
project mercury.

10:22.489 --> 10:24.589
I screened his e-mail,
listened in on calls.

10:24.591 --> 10:27.125
Everything checked out.
He checked out!

10:27.127 --> 10:29.894
There has got to be
another explanation.

10:29.896 --> 10:31.663
Billy did not do this.

10:31.665 --> 10:33.765
I get why she wouldn't want
billy to be a suspect.

10:33.767 --> 10:35.333
If she accuses him
and she's wrong,

10:35.335 --> 10:36.835
She ruins her relationship.

10:36.837 --> 10:39.270
If she accuses him and she's
right, she ruins her career.

10:39.272 --> 10:41.272
Do we think that's possible,
that billy didn't do it?

10:41.274 --> 10:42.641
-He did it.
-He did it.

10:42.643 --> 10:44.009
The only question is...

10:44.011 --> 10:46.478
Is diane's boyfriend a spy
or a whistle-blower?

10:46.480 --> 10:48.213
Let's get to work, people.

10:57.824 --> 10:59.090
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

10:59.092 --> 11:00.825
[ sighs ]

11:00.827 --> 11:02.694
Mm. Can I have some?

11:02.696 --> 11:04.029
No.

11:04.031 --> 11:07.432
[ sighs ]

11:07.434 --> 11:08.433
[ cellphone chiming ]

11:08.435 --> 11:09.534
Ohh.

11:09.536 --> 11:11.703
[ chiming continues ]

11:18.478 --> 11:19.477
[ cellphone beeps ]

11:19.479 --> 11:21.212
Cyrus.

11:21.214 --> 11:23.848
Look, I need an opinion.

11:23.850 --> 11:25.784
-Cyrus, I can't.
-Just quick,

11:25.786 --> 11:27.519
One of your liv-pinions.

11:27.521 --> 11:28.319
So, listen --

11:28.321 --> 11:29.654
Cyrus, stop talking.

11:29.656 --> 11:31.723
The days of the two of us
talking on the phone

11:31.725 --> 11:33.792
Late into the night like besties
ended a long time ago.

11:33.794 --> 11:34.893
Goodbye.

11:34.895 --> 11:36.728
Abby!
This is about abby.

11:36.730 --> 11:38.029
You like abby.

11:38.031 --> 11:40.065
Abby's still a, uh,
bestie, right?

11:43.537 --> 11:45.370
20 seconds.

11:46.640 --> 11:49.174
I just want to know, do you
think she's got it in her --

11:49.176 --> 11:50.308
Work wife?

11:50.310 --> 11:51.309
Work wife full-on?

11:51.311 --> 11:53.078
Can she handle it?

11:53.080 --> 11:56.247
[ sighs ]

11:56.249 --> 11:57.716
Cy, you're still there,

11:57.718 --> 12:00.585
So this is just a pointless
hypothetical exercise.

12:00.587 --> 12:02.353
Liv, you and I both know
I'm no longer in the room.

12:02.355 --> 12:03.054
I'm outside the door.

12:03.056 --> 12:04.522
[ breathes shakily ]

12:04.524 --> 12:06.524
Abby.

12:06.526 --> 12:08.493
Can she handle it?

12:14.935 --> 12:17.502
Yes, abby can handle it.

12:17.504 --> 12:19.270
Thank you. [ sighs ]
what I needed to hear.

12:19.272 --> 12:20.371
But...

12:20.373 --> 12:21.906
But what?

12:24.511 --> 12:26.177
That's a lot of power, cy.

12:26.179 --> 12:28.847
That's --
that's the oval.

12:29.916 --> 12:30.915
Be sure.

12:30.917 --> 12:33.551
Before you give that up,

12:33.553 --> 12:35.987
Be sure.

12:42.129 --> 12:43.161
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

12:47.400 --> 12:48.433
Liv --

12:48.435 --> 12:49.801
What leads do we have
on billy?

12:49.803 --> 12:50.935
-Uh, liv?
-Diane is in denial.

12:50.937 --> 12:52.437
Mellie grant
is in your office.

12:52.439 --> 12:53.805
A woman's career is at stake,
and we need to know if --

12:53.807 --> 12:54.906
Wait. What?
What did you say?

12:54.908 --> 12:55.673
Mellie grant is...

12:57.711 --> 12:59.344
I see that.

13:03.784 --> 13:05.316
[ sighs ]

13:05.318 --> 13:06.651
You wrote a book.

13:06.653 --> 13:07.986
I wrote a book.

13:07.988 --> 13:09.821
A book.<i> My</i> book.

13:09.823 --> 13:11.389
My open letter
to the country.

13:11.391 --> 13:13.324
My statement of beliefs
and hopes.

13:13.326 --> 13:15.960
This is me tossing my ante
into the center of the table,

13:15.962 --> 13:17.328
Airing out all
my dirty laundry

13:17.330 --> 13:19.397
So it's old news by the time
the campaign rolls around.

13:19.399 --> 13:21.299
That way, I'm not constantly
hounded with questions

13:21.301 --> 13:22.333
About my involvement
in our...

13:22.335 --> 13:24.602
Sordid little
white house love triangle

13:24.604 --> 13:26.604
When we rope-line
in new hampshire.

13:26.606 --> 13:27.939
I'm not running
your campaign.

13:27.941 --> 13:30.475
Just...Give it a read.

13:30.477 --> 13:31.676
Let me know
what you think.

13:31.678 --> 13:32.844
That would be me working
for you.

13:32.846 --> 13:33.845
I'll pay you, obviously.

13:33.847 --> 13:34.846
I can't accept.

13:34.848 --> 13:36.681
Then call it a favor.

13:38.485 --> 13:40.618
I'm just gonna leave it here
with you...

13:40.620 --> 13:42.987
Mellie.

13:42.989 --> 13:44.422
...And whenever
you get a chance --

13:44.424 --> 13:46.224
Preferably by Thursday --
you'll tell me what you think.

13:49.830 --> 13:50.962
[ camera shutters clicking ]

13:50.964 --> 13:52.297
[ reporters clamoring ]

13:52.299 --> 13:54.532
That's all for now.
Thank you.

13:54.534 --> 13:56.768
Abby.
Nelson.

13:56.770 --> 13:58.169
You haven't called on me
all week.

13:58.171 --> 14:00.104
If I can't get my questions
answered, I can't do my job.

14:00.106 --> 14:02.307
Should've thought about that
before you wrote that hit piece

14:02.309 --> 14:03.308
On the president's
energy plan.

14:03.310 --> 14:04.275
What if I can
make up for it?

14:04.277 --> 14:05.210
That would take
a retraction.

14:05.212 --> 14:06.611
Are you offering me
a retraction?

14:06.613 --> 14:07.412
You know about project
mercury, right?

14:09.549 --> 14:10.849
What about it?

14:10.851 --> 14:12.684
Some nsa whistle-blower
called our publisher,

14:12.686 --> 14:14.352
Offered her a chance to read
through a treasure trove

14:14.354 --> 14:16.020
Of stolen documents,
chief among them --

14:16.022 --> 14:17.455
Project mercury.
[ scoffing ] yeah.

14:17.457 --> 14:18.556
Already on it,
my friend.

14:18.558 --> 14:20.391
You want out
of my doghouse,

14:20.393 --> 14:23.461
You're gonna have to try
harder than that.

14:23.463 --> 14:26.297
What the hell
is project mercury?

14:26.299 --> 14:28.633
Someone get me a folder!

14:30.136 --> 14:33.538
[ breathing heavily ]

14:33.540 --> 14:36.474
The<i> post</i> knows we're spying
on foreign leaders, allies,

14:36.476 --> 14:38.142
Tapping right into
their personal phones.

14:38.144 --> 14:39.510
[ sighs ]

14:39.512 --> 14:41.512
If this whistle-blower
comes through

14:41.514 --> 14:42.981
And gives them
project mercury,

14:42.983 --> 14:44.349
Then the<i> post</i>
will know everything.

14:44.351 --> 14:48.386
Cyrus, do you want
to add anything?

14:48.388 --> 14:50.188
That ain't good.

14:50.190 --> 14:52.490
What's your plan
for shutting this down?

14:52.492 --> 14:53.892
I, uh...

14:53.894 --> 14:55.493
[ sighs ]

14:55.495 --> 14:56.861
Olivia: Hey. Do not tell me
you are canceling on me.

14:56.863 --> 14:57.896
I'm not canceling on you.

14:57.898 --> 14:59.597
What do you know
about jillian foster?

14:59.599 --> 15:02.400
I worked with jillian
on the judge elliot thing.

15:02.402 --> 15:04.269
Right. Well,
what's her deal?

15:04.271 --> 15:06.337
Tough, smart, tiny chip
on her shoulder

15:06.339 --> 15:08.506
After inheriting the<i> post</i>
from her dad, but --

15:08.508 --> 15:10.375
So she has something to prove?

15:10.377 --> 15:11.676
What are you guys
trying to shut down?

15:11.678 --> 15:14.579
Uh, just a little national
security story.

15:14.581 --> 15:16.614
You're calling in
the publisher of the<i> post</i>

15:16.616 --> 15:18.583
To shut down a little
national security story?

15:18.585 --> 15:19.550
I'm going, liv.

15:19.552 --> 15:21.119
Sorry. Old habits.

15:21.121 --> 15:22.620
No worries.
See you tomorrow night.

15:22.622 --> 15:25.123
Billy took project mercury
to the<i> post.</i>

15:25.125 --> 15:26.791
Then they must not have
the documents yet.

15:26.793 --> 15:28.459
If they did, they would've
already published them.

15:28.461 --> 15:29.928
Track him down.
Retrace his steps.

15:29.930 --> 15:32.230
Do whatever you need to do
to find billy and stop him

15:32.232 --> 15:33.865
Before he's able
to hand over what he has.

15:37.203 --> 15:38.970
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

15:47.113 --> 15:49.447
I have got to get me
one of these.

15:49.449 --> 15:50.949
Thanks for coming.

15:53.453 --> 15:55.420
You're working.
You seem good.

15:55.422 --> 15:57.555
What? You thought
you'd find me drunk,

15:57.557 --> 15:59.958
Playing russian roulette
with the nuclear codes?

15:59.960 --> 16:02.093
[ chuckling ] you did.

16:02.095 --> 16:03.828
You didn't vote for me,
did you?

16:03.830 --> 16:06.764
[ laughs ]

16:06.766 --> 16:09.233
No, I'm good.
I'm...

16:09.235 --> 16:12.136
I have my freedom.

16:12.138 --> 16:14.439
I'm focused.

16:14.441 --> 16:17.308
Abby says I'm "all cylinders,"
whatever that means.

16:19.846 --> 16:22.246
So, why am I here?

16:26.019 --> 16:28.252
I have a problem
with the<i> post.</i>

16:28.254 --> 16:29.754
What do they have?

16:32.492 --> 16:35.526
Project mercury.

16:35.528 --> 16:37.662
The nsa spy project.
Mother--

16:37.664 --> 16:40.198
The<i> post</i> could run with it --
front page.

16:40.200 --> 16:42.133
A diplomatic nightmare.

16:42.135 --> 16:44.268
The g20 alone --
-yeah, so much for allies.

16:44.270 --> 16:46.537
The united states will be alone
in the world.

16:46.539 --> 16:49.674
That is a very dark street
to walk every night.

16:49.676 --> 16:53.111
[ sighs ]
how'd the<i> post</i> get the story?

16:53.113 --> 16:55.546
That's the problem.

16:57.717 --> 16:59.384
Okay. [ sighs ]

16:59.386 --> 17:01.719
The only way something
as deep cover as mercury

17:01.721 --> 17:03.488
Gets out
is from the inside.

17:03.490 --> 17:05.456
You have a whistle-blower
at the nsa.

17:05.458 --> 17:06.991
Which is why I need you
to handle this.

17:06.993 --> 17:08.159
Keep it off
the agency's radar.

17:08.161 --> 17:10.461
Why me?

17:10.463 --> 17:13.464
I need someone I trust.

17:13.466 --> 17:14.866
[ scoffs ]

17:14.868 --> 17:16.734
I'm not the obvious
choice, then.

17:16.736 --> 17:18.569
You and I both know
that's not true.

17:23.176 --> 17:24.976
You don't talk to her?

17:28.081 --> 17:29.580
No.

17:31.317 --> 17:33.985
I don't.

17:33.987 --> 17:35.653
You?

17:35.655 --> 17:37.855
No...

17:37.857 --> 17:39.223
I don't.

17:39.225 --> 17:40.258
[ liquid pours ]

17:43.696 --> 17:46.564
I'm in for the job.
[ sighs ]

17:46.566 --> 17:48.299
Thank you.

17:54.741 --> 17:58.042
I really have to get myself
this view.

17:58.044 --> 18:00.411
Only one way
to get<i> this</i> view.

18:00.413 --> 18:02.346
And trust me,
it's a bitch.

18:09.923 --> 18:11.856
[ cellphone ringing ]

18:18.465 --> 18:19.697
Hello, mr. President.

18:19.699 --> 18:21.365
Hey.

18:21.367 --> 18:23.367
Did you know you could get
gettysburger french fries

18:23.369 --> 18:24.569
In a bag
from the grocery store?

18:24.571 --> 18:25.870
Yes, sir.

18:25.872 --> 18:27.572
Freedom fries --
right from the store.

18:27.574 --> 18:28.940
You just put them
in the microwave.

18:28.942 --> 18:30.141
I'm eating them
right now.

18:30.143 --> 18:31.242
That's wonderful, sir.

18:31.244 --> 18:32.743
Anyway,
the middle east papers.

18:32.745 --> 18:34.879
I was thinking we should focus
on soft power

18:34.881 --> 18:36.414
Instead of
taking a hard stance.

18:36.416 --> 18:38.015
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

18:41.087 --> 18:43.554
[ sighs ]

18:43.556 --> 18:45.723
Red!
I'm very busy right now.

18:45.725 --> 18:47.258
Are you punishing me?

18:47.260 --> 18:49.560
Are you mad at me?
Did I do something?

18:49.562 --> 18:50.828
Truffle?

18:50.830 --> 18:53.464
[ sighs ]
he's driving me crazy.

18:53.466 --> 18:55.266
He's calling me
24 hours a day.

18:55.268 --> 18:57.101
I can exist on four hours
of sleep,

18:57.103 --> 18:58.903
But he's whittled me down
to 3 1/2.

18:58.905 --> 19:01.672
What kind of human being only
needs 3 1/2 hours of sleep?

19:01.674 --> 19:02.673
He calls and calls

19:02.675 --> 19:04.675
With questions and ideas
and thoughts.

19:04.677 --> 19:06.577
And the other day,
he wanted me

19:06.579 --> 19:08.646
To explain the backstory
for a tv show.

19:08.648 --> 19:11.282
Then I come in to work,
and he talks only to me.

19:11.284 --> 19:12.283
<i> Only</i> to me.

19:12.285 --> 19:13.417
I have a job.

19:13.419 --> 19:14.585
I have to be
on the podium.

19:14.587 --> 19:16.621
I have to be prepared
and run the room.

19:16.623 --> 19:18.523
I can't be prepared.
I can't run the room.

19:18.525 --> 19:19.957
I have to go and listen
to him talk!

19:19.959 --> 19:22.026
I am tired, cyrus!

19:22.028 --> 19:25.329
I am exhausted because he won't
stop talking to me.

19:25.331 --> 19:27.298
And I don't know what's wrong
with him.

19:27.300 --> 19:29.600
He's broken or he needs
his batteries replaced

19:29.602 --> 19:30.868
Or the little wind-up thing
in his back

19:30.870 --> 19:31.969
Needs to be turned again,

19:31.971 --> 19:34.172
And I can't figure out
how to fix it!

19:34.174 --> 19:36.440
And now one of our
top-secret spy programs

19:36.442 --> 19:38.109
Is about to be leaked
to the world,

19:38.111 --> 19:40.211
And I can't figure out
how to fix that, either.

19:40.213 --> 19:41.646
Why? Because
you won't help me.

19:41.648 --> 19:44.282
Why aren't you helping me?

19:46.719 --> 19:49.620
Marriage, red, can wreak havoc
on a person.

19:49.622 --> 19:51.489
What are you --

19:51.491 --> 19:53.491
[ chuckling ]
you're his new work wife!

19:53.493 --> 19:55.793
The shiny new bride
who's just been

19:55.795 --> 19:59.330
Carried across the threshold
of the oval.

19:59.332 --> 20:00.798
You're his new wife.

20:00.800 --> 20:02.967
Ew. No, I am not.

20:02.969 --> 20:04.235
The man needs a wife.

20:04.237 --> 20:05.469
He always has,
and he always will.

20:05.471 --> 20:06.637
He can't function
any other way.

20:06.639 --> 20:08.072
He is not meant
to be alone.

20:08.074 --> 20:09.974
He doesn't know how.

20:09.976 --> 20:11.475
He needs a wife.

20:11.477 --> 20:13.177
It can't be liv anymore
because she's gone.

20:13.179 --> 20:17.148
Mellie was a great one
for all her faults.

20:17.150 --> 20:19.917
I was brilliant at it,
but it can't be me anymore.

20:19.919 --> 20:22.353
Betrayal's still there.

20:22.355 --> 20:23.588
Well, he forgave you.

20:25.725 --> 20:26.657
[ scoffs ]

20:26.659 --> 20:27.558
Cyrus.

20:27.560 --> 20:28.693
I can't help you.

20:28.695 --> 20:30.194
You're the new wife.

20:30.196 --> 20:33.064
Anything I say taints
your honeymoon.

20:33.066 --> 20:36.334
You need to find your own way
in this marriage, red.

20:36.336 --> 20:38.336
Godspeed.

20:40.073 --> 20:41.439
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

20:44.210 --> 20:45.843
Any luck
tracking down billy?

20:45.845 --> 20:47.278
Nope. Nada.

20:47.280 --> 20:48.579
We checked his house,
went by his office --

20:48.581 --> 20:49.413
No one's seen him
in a couple days.

20:49.415 --> 20:50.681
What about you?

20:50.683 --> 20:52.083
I'm running a program to
pinpoint his cell signal.

20:52.085 --> 20:53.351
Got it.

20:53.353 --> 20:55.219
He's about 30 miles away
and moving.

20:55.221 --> 20:56.854
Text me a nearby address.

20:56.856 --> 20:57.622
Where are you going?

20:57.624 --> 20:58.956
With her.

20:58.958 --> 21:00.224
No, you're not.

21:00.226 --> 21:01.225
Yeah, huck's right. This guy
could be dangerous.

21:01.227 --> 21:02.059
You're more of
an office guy.

21:02.061 --> 21:03.394
Then I'll hide behind her,

21:03.396 --> 21:04.095
But I'm going.

21:04.097 --> 21:05.696
Fine. Your funeral.

21:05.698 --> 21:06.931
[ sighs ]

21:06.933 --> 21:08.699
Supportive co-workers --
nothing like it.

21:08.701 --> 21:10.434
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

21:14.607 --> 21:16.440
You sure this is
the address?

21:16.442 --> 21:18.542
No, marcus,
just a wild guess.

21:18.544 --> 21:20.878
Here. You deal.
Haters gonna hate.

21:20.880 --> 21:22.413
Look, there's nothing
here, huck.

21:22.415 --> 21:23.981
Well, that's where
the signal is.

21:23.983 --> 21:25.249
[ light rustling ]

21:25.251 --> 21:26.851
Wait a minute.
I think he's here.

21:32.425 --> 21:34.025
You looking for this?

21:36.663 --> 21:37.962
What were you doing
in that house?

21:37.964 --> 21:39.764
Same thing as you -- looking
for william torrance.

21:39.766 --> 21:41.499
The only difference is I'm
working for the president,

21:41.501 --> 21:43.267
And you're working for the woman
who was stupid enough

21:43.269 --> 21:44.168
To let a traitor
into her home.

21:44.170 --> 21:45.436
Fitz put you on this?

21:45.438 --> 21:47.238
I'm helping out
where I can.

21:47.240 --> 21:48.606
In this case,
the white house got a tip

21:48.608 --> 21:50.107
That torrance was pulling
a snowden.

21:50.109 --> 21:51.309
His first stop
was the<i> post.</i>

21:51.311 --> 21:52.777
His last stop was
that charming bungalow,

21:52.779 --> 21:54.245
Where he obviously
dumped his phone

21:54.247 --> 21:55.680
In order to throw everyone
off his scent.

21:55.682 --> 21:57.848
That doesn't make any sense.
Why break into a house?

21:57.850 --> 21:59.583
Why not just throw the phone
in a trash can somewhere?

21:59.585 --> 22:00.518
I don't know.

22:00.520 --> 22:01.752
Maybe he was
gonna come back,

22:01.754 --> 22:03.120
Fix the place up,
and retire there

22:03.122 --> 22:04.121
With all the money he made

22:04.123 --> 22:05.623
From selling all
the top-secret files

22:05.625 --> 22:07.358
He stole out from under
your client's nose.

22:07.360 --> 22:08.826
Billy hasn't done
anything yet.

22:08.828 --> 22:10.494
He may be flirting
with the<i> post,</i>

22:10.496 --> 22:11.962
But he hasn't sold or leaked
any files.

22:11.964 --> 22:13.364
[ chuckling ] so?

22:13.366 --> 22:14.865
So, that information
isn't out there,

22:14.867 --> 22:17.368
Which means we still have a
chance to stop him before it is.

22:17.370 --> 22:18.636
There is no "we" here,
olivia!

22:18.638 --> 22:19.937
I'm not helping you
cover up

22:19.939 --> 22:21.539
For a client who made
a huge mistake!

22:21.541 --> 22:23.274
Oh, come on. We both know
that happens all the time.

22:23.276 --> 22:24.775
Her only mistake was falling
for the wrong guy.

22:24.777 --> 22:27.111
Oh, well, no wonder you're
so sympathetic to her cause.

22:27.113 --> 22:29.180
-Jake --
-liv, stop!

22:29.182 --> 22:31.515
Your guy is guilty,
so save the spinning.

22:31.517 --> 22:33.784
It's beneath you,
and it's an insult to me.

22:33.786 --> 22:35.119
Where are you going?

22:35.121 --> 22:36.887
I win. You lose.

22:36.889 --> 22:37.988
So does your client.

22:37.990 --> 22:39.857
[ sighs ]

22:39.859 --> 22:41.892
♪♪

22:45.665 --> 22:48.332
They're from the office
of the inspector general.

22:48.334 --> 22:51.068
I'm officially
under investigation.

22:55.208 --> 22:58.242
There was a call to the<i> post</i>
on billy's cellphone.

22:58.244 --> 23:00.244
I know that's not the news
you were hoping for,

23:00.246 --> 23:01.479
But that's what they found.

23:01.481 --> 23:03.414
I'm very good at my job,

23:03.416 --> 23:05.649
And they're going to say
he preyed on my loneliness.

23:05.651 --> 23:07.885
I like to think I'm stronger
than that.

23:07.887 --> 23:11.255
It's not easy finding someone
when you're a general.

23:11.257 --> 23:13.190
Men find my stars
threatening.

23:13.192 --> 23:14.759
But not billy.

23:14.761 --> 23:18.829
He looked at me and saw a woman,
a partner.

23:18.831 --> 23:22.433
At least that's what
I thought he saw.

23:22.435 --> 23:24.902
I guess what he really saw
was opportunity.

23:27.039 --> 23:29.507
They're gonna fire me,
aren't they?

23:29.509 --> 23:32.443
They're looking to see if you
and billy collaborated.

23:32.445 --> 23:35.546
You didn't, so criminally
speaking, you're fine.

23:35.548 --> 23:36.680
In terms of your job,
however --

23:36.682 --> 23:37.915
What if you talked
to the president?

23:37.917 --> 23:40.084
I don't think that's --

23:40.086 --> 23:42.253
If the president fires me,
that's it.

23:42.255 --> 23:44.688
I won't just be the first
female nsa director.

23:44.690 --> 23:45.790
I'll be the last.

23:45.792 --> 23:47.124
They'll use me
as an example,

23:47.126 --> 23:48.859
Say our hearts
make us weak.

23:48.861 --> 23:50.928
For the next 20, 30,
50 years,

23:50.930 --> 23:53.397
The only candidates they'll
consider will be men.

23:53.399 --> 23:55.933
I made a mistake, liv,

23:55.935 --> 23:57.935
And I deserve
to be punished.

23:57.937 --> 24:00.538
Just not if it means punishing
our entire sex.

24:01.808 --> 24:03.707
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

24:07.814 --> 24:09.814
[ cellphone rings ]

24:09.816 --> 24:11.715
[ cellphone beeps ]

24:11.717 --> 24:13.584
Yes, mr. President.

24:13.586 --> 24:15.419
I got the advance copy of
prime minister cho's remarks

24:15.421 --> 24:16.720
To the u.N.
Security council.

24:16.722 --> 24:18.389
Thought we could hunker down,
take a look.

24:20.293 --> 24:22.460
Uh, I'm sorry, sir.
I can't.

24:22.462 --> 24:25.095
I'm, uh, at the hospital
with leo.

24:25.097 --> 24:26.497
Who are you talking to?

24:26.499 --> 24:28.399
-He all right?
-Yeah.

24:28.401 --> 24:30.134
Turns out, that flu
might be pneumonia.

24:30.136 --> 24:31.435
Nothing too serious.

24:31.437 --> 24:32.169
Pneumonia can be
very serious.

24:32.171 --> 24:33.437
Keep me posted.

24:33.439 --> 24:35.072
Yes, sir. I will.
Thank you.

24:35.074 --> 24:37.374
[ cellphone beeps ]

24:39.145 --> 24:40.945
I stole some scotch
from his collection.

24:40.947 --> 24:41.912
Good.

24:44.350 --> 24:47.351
Mmm, this is<i> so</i> good.

24:47.353 --> 24:48.652
[ laughs ]

24:48.654 --> 24:51.489
You have no idea how much
I have needed this --

24:51.491 --> 24:53.591
Silence...

24:53.593 --> 24:55.626
Adult conversation --
not about politics --

24:55.628 --> 24:57.161
Eating in peace.

24:57.163 --> 24:59.396
Yeah, when I came home,
I couldn't get enough of it.

25:04.170 --> 25:06.170
You miss him?

25:06.172 --> 25:08.939
No.

25:08.941 --> 25:12.877
I mean,
I do, but I don't.

25:12.879 --> 25:15.646
I'm talking about the work,
the speed of a political day,

25:15.648 --> 25:17.848
The energy, the pace.

25:17.850 --> 25:19.984
It's a rush.

25:19.986 --> 25:22.219
Leo wants me
to quit my job.

25:22.221 --> 25:23.954
What?
Abby, you can't quit.

25:23.956 --> 25:26.690
Leo, by the way, he took
a campaign in texas.

25:26.692 --> 25:28.692
He hates texas,
but he took it

25:28.694 --> 25:30.828
Because he says
it didn't matter,

25:30.830 --> 25:33.898
He never sees me anyway,
and I was ready to get mad,

25:33.900 --> 25:35.866
But...He's right.

25:35.868 --> 25:37.067
I mean, this job is --

25:37.069 --> 25:37.902
You can't quit.

25:37.904 --> 25:39.036
I know I can't quit.

25:39.038 --> 25:41.138
It's the white house.

25:41.140 --> 25:42.973
But I'm the work wife,
liv.

25:42.975 --> 25:45.142
He's work-wifing the hell
out of me.

25:45.144 --> 25:48.245
Work wife's a good thing.
It means you've got his ear.

25:48.247 --> 25:50.180
It means I've got no life.

25:50.182 --> 25:53.651
And I barely had one before,
but this...

25:53.653 --> 25:57.688
I mean, what is
the man's problem?

25:57.690 --> 26:00.024
Liv, I know that it was bad
and it was awful

26:00.026 --> 26:01.325
And painful and sad,

26:01.327 --> 26:05.529
But, just,
at 2:00 in the morning,

26:05.531 --> 26:08.566
I can't feel<i> that</i> sorry
for the rich, handsome,

26:08.568 --> 26:10.401
Powerful leader
of the free world

26:10.403 --> 26:12.703
Who got his heart broken
and now he's lonely.

26:12.705 --> 26:15.873
Abby, he's not lonely.
He's alone.

26:15.875 --> 26:18.075
He doesn't have anyone.

26:18.077 --> 26:20.210
I was it.

26:20.212 --> 26:23.347
I was the last person
he trusted --

26:23.349 --> 26:25.449
The last person he had.

26:25.451 --> 26:27.585
He doesn't have anyone.

26:27.587 --> 26:31.522
Oh.
Now I feel like an ass.

26:33.526 --> 26:35.726
I need to call him.

26:35.728 --> 26:37.261
Not for you or me.

26:37.263 --> 26:40.598
He may be the only out
I have for my client.

26:40.600 --> 26:44.068
But it would be unfair of me
to ask for a favor.

26:44.070 --> 26:46.470
I don't want to --
I can't do that to him.

26:46.472 --> 26:48.572
I can't put him
in that position.

26:48.574 --> 26:51.909
So, you're not gonna call

26:51.911 --> 26:55.212
Because you're being respectful
of his feelings?

26:55.214 --> 26:57.081
Yeah.

26:57.083 --> 27:00.417
Sorry. I'm just not drunk enough
to buy it.

27:00.419 --> 27:03.420
You're afraid he actually
might pick up the phone,

27:03.422 --> 27:05.322
That he might
do you a favor,

27:05.324 --> 27:07.391
That you might end up
owing him,

27:07.393 --> 27:09.560
And that he might
call you again,

27:09.562 --> 27:12.596
And you're back to square one,
for better or for worse.

27:12.598 --> 27:14.798
You're terrified.

27:17.737 --> 27:21.271
I would tell you or anyone else
to suck it up, get over it.

27:21.273 --> 27:22.740
I'd say,
"quit being a baby.

27:22.742 --> 27:24.441
Stop thinking
about yourself

27:24.443 --> 27:27.311
And pick up the phone and do
what is best for your client."

27:27.313 --> 27:29.113
Excellent
olivia pope advice.

27:29.115 --> 27:31.382
Then why don't I seem to be able
to take it?

27:34.286 --> 27:38.389
♪ when darkness comes ♪

27:42.161 --> 27:44.762
Looked through
the guy's e-mail?

27:44.764 --> 27:46.964
The whistle-blower?
Uh, yeah.

27:46.966 --> 27:49.366
Work, personal --
nothing there.

27:49.368 --> 27:52.169
Check flight manifests?
Tollbooth cams?

27:52.171 --> 27:55.839
Yes, he didn't come up.

27:55.841 --> 27:58.008
There weren't any suspicious
transactions on his credit card?

27:58.010 --> 27:58.942
No!

27:58.944 --> 28:00.310
Sorry.

28:00.312 --> 28:02.713
I'm just...Impressed.

28:02.715 --> 28:06.984
Guy's great at disappearing
for a whistle-blower.

28:06.986 --> 28:09.153
He's got
some serious game.

28:09.155 --> 28:10.187
[ exhales sharply ]

28:12.491 --> 28:13.857
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

28:13.859 --> 28:19.930
♪ I will lay me down ♪

28:28.708 --> 28:30.107
[ sighs ]

28:36.582 --> 28:41.218
♪ sail on, silver girl ♪

28:43.656 --> 28:47.558
Hi, charlotte.
It's olivia -- pope.

28:47.560 --> 28:49.426
Is the president in?

28:54.166 --> 28:56.533
Sir?

28:56.535 --> 28:58.402
Miss pope is on the line
for you.

29:02.675 --> 29:06.276
♪ to shine ♪

29:08.547 --> 29:17.855
♪ and all your dreams
are on their way ♪

29:17.857 --> 29:20.524
I'm sorry.
The president's not available.

29:20.526 --> 29:22.292
Would you like
to leave a message?

29:22.294 --> 29:25.462
No. Thanks, charlotte.

29:25.464 --> 29:27.364
[ cellphone beeps ]

29:32.138 --> 29:33.504
♪ if you... ♪

29:38.244 --> 29:39.209
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

29:39.211 --> 29:41.612
[ cellphone ringing ]

29:41.614 --> 29:43.814
Ugh.

29:43.816 --> 29:45.449
No.

29:47.953 --> 29:48.819
[ ringing stops ]

29:48.821 --> 29:51.655
[ sighs ]

29:51.657 --> 29:56.960
Five, four, three, two...

29:56.962 --> 29:57.761
[ cellphone rings ]

29:57.763 --> 29:58.829
[ sighs ]

29:58.831 --> 30:00.330
[ cellphone beeps ]

30:00.332 --> 30:01.899
Morning, mr. President.

30:01.901 --> 30:04.501
No, I didn't hear
the phone before.

30:04.503 --> 30:07.604
Yeah, I am happy to talk
nsa director candidates.

30:07.606 --> 30:10.407
Uh-huh.

30:10.409 --> 30:13.076
Uh-huh, sir.

30:13.078 --> 30:14.745
Uh-huh. Uh-huh.

30:44.443 --> 30:45.576
[ sighs ]

31:01.060 --> 31:02.559
[ sighs ]

31:07.666 --> 31:09.466
Make sure you lock up
on your way out.

31:09.468 --> 31:11.134
You forgot last time.

31:13.138 --> 31:15.572
[ door opens, closes ]

31:15.574 --> 31:17.007
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

31:17.009 --> 31:18.976
-What are you up to?
-[ sighs ] you were right.

31:18.978 --> 31:20.577
Billy's insanely crafty
for your average

31:20.579 --> 31:21.912
Boyfriend-turned-whistle-blower.

31:21.914 --> 31:23.647
There's got to be
something else going on,

31:23.649 --> 31:25.315
So I've been trying
to crack my way

31:25.317 --> 31:26.817
Into the<i> post</i>
voicemail system,

31:26.819 --> 31:28.318
See if I can get a listen
to the first call

31:28.320 --> 31:29.419
Billy made to the paper.

31:29.421 --> 31:31.521
Sharp.

31:31.523 --> 31:32.823
I'm not having much luck.

31:32.825 --> 31:35.158
They say the newspaper business
is dead broke,

31:35.160 --> 31:37.761
But you couldn't tell by this
ridiculous level of encryption.

31:37.763 --> 31:40.097
Didn't the virus that hacked
into the nsa chick's home system

31:40.099 --> 31:42.099
Do the kind of thing you're
trying to do right now?

31:44.036 --> 31:45.068
That might work.

31:45.070 --> 31:46.570
Come on, robin.

31:46.572 --> 31:47.704
Who says we're not
the dream team?

31:47.706 --> 31:50.674
[ scoffs ]

31:50.676 --> 31:51.875
So, it's all clear?

31:51.877 --> 31:54.111
'cause I don't want any problems
with this one.

31:54.113 --> 31:55.579
Everything's clean.

31:55.581 --> 31:57.080
His background's perfect.
I did it myself.

31:57.082 --> 31:58.949
He'll sail through
any nomination hearings.

31:58.951 --> 32:00.550
Here's your speech.

32:00.552 --> 32:02.853
Remember -- shake, commendation,
shake again.

32:07.092 --> 32:11.028
Fitz:
Late last night, I asked for
and received the resignation

32:11.030 --> 32:13.630
Of nsa director lieutenant
general diane peters.

32:13.632 --> 32:15.532
I'm so sorry, diane,
but you should know

32:15.534 --> 32:18.135
That pope and associates is here
to help you transition

32:18.137 --> 32:21.438
To the public sector
or private life if you prefer.

32:21.440 --> 32:23.140
That's not exactly
why I hired you.

32:23.142 --> 32:24.141
What did he say?

32:24.143 --> 32:25.208
What did<i> who</i> say?

32:25.210 --> 32:26.777
The president.

32:28.447 --> 32:30.948
He was unhelpful.

32:30.950 --> 32:32.983
[ sighs ]

32:32.985 --> 32:35.452
Maybe you could get me
into the oval,

32:35.454 --> 32:37.821
Speak with him,
plead my case in person.

32:37.823 --> 32:41.825
I think we need to prepare
for your next step.

32:41.827 --> 32:44.461
Right.

32:47.299 --> 32:50.500
How about you just tell me
who they're replacing me with?

32:50.502 --> 32:52.402
I'm sure the president is
putting together a list.

32:52.404 --> 32:55.105
List?

32:55.107 --> 32:56.640
They already have someone.

32:56.642 --> 32:58.809
An old crony
of the president's.

32:58.811 --> 33:01.511
I just wanted the name.

33:01.513 --> 33:04.715
And I thought
<i> I</i> was out of the loop.

33:06.118 --> 33:08.986
Our safety and the intelligence
within our borders

33:08.988 --> 33:10.787
Is of the utmost importance.

33:10.789 --> 33:13.991
The nsa allows americans
to sleep safe in their beds,

33:13.993 --> 33:16.893
Knowing that a greater power
is watching out for them.

33:24.336 --> 33:26.269
It wasn't billy.

33:26.271 --> 33:27.504
What are you
talking about?

33:27.506 --> 33:29.206
The whistle-blower --
it wasn't billy.

33:29.208 --> 33:31.308
I listened to the voicemail
billy supposedly left the<i> post.</i>

33:31.310 --> 33:33.343
The caller used a scrambler
to mask his identity --

33:33.345 --> 33:34.678
Said it was for
his own protection.

33:34.680 --> 33:35.979
And you unscrambled it?

33:35.981 --> 33:37.781
No, but I downloaded a bunch
of messages diane received

33:37.783 --> 33:39.549
From billy and compared
speech patterns.

33:39.551 --> 33:41.618
The rhythm, the cadence --
it's completely different.

33:41.620 --> 33:43.320
There's no way that the person
who called the<i> post</i>

33:43.322 --> 33:44.187
And billy are the same.

33:44.189 --> 33:45.122
Then who is the caller?

33:45.124 --> 33:46.690
I don't know.

33:46.692 --> 33:48.291
Someone who was trying
to set billy up.

33:56.735 --> 33:59.569
Abby, who's he replacing
diane peters with?

33:59.571 --> 34:02.172
Who's the next head
of the nsa?

34:02.174 --> 34:04.241
Today I will be placing
the nation's security

34:04.243 --> 34:07.210
Into the hands of a person
who has earned this job

34:07.212 --> 34:10.414
Through unparalleled service
to his country.

34:10.416 --> 34:12.382
Where did jake come from
when you saw him here?

34:12.384 --> 34:13.817
What room was
he coming from?

34:13.819 --> 34:14.918
He came from that hallway.

34:14.920 --> 34:17.487
Fitz:
He's a scholar with degrees

34:17.489 --> 34:19.122
From annapolis and harvard.

34:24.196 --> 34:26.596
♪♪

34:29.201 --> 34:31.001
[ refrigerator rattling ]

34:32.538 --> 34:33.437
Huck!

34:33.439 --> 34:35.072
He's also a navy seal

34:35.074 --> 34:36.940
And a decorated war hero.

34:36.942 --> 34:38.909
I would trust him with my life.

34:38.911 --> 34:41.445
In fact, I already have.
That's how he became a war hero.

34:43.015 --> 34:44.681
[ gasps ]

34:44.683 --> 34:47.517
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

34:47.519 --> 34:49.019
What the hell?

34:50.889 --> 34:52.889
[ exhales sharply ]

34:52.891 --> 34:55.058
Jake wasn't searching
for billy.

34:55.060 --> 34:56.526
He was disposing of him.

34:59.364 --> 35:01.598
Jake killed billy.

35:01.600 --> 35:04.301
His career in public service
includes high-level work

35:04.303 --> 35:06.703
At the pentagon
for the defense department

35:06.705 --> 35:09.539
As well as his work
as an intelligence advisor

35:09.541 --> 35:11.908
To the white house,
which is short for,

35:11.910 --> 35:14.444
"he could tell you exactly
what all that means,

35:14.446 --> 35:15.946
But then he'd have to kill ya."

35:15.948 --> 35:17.280
[ laughter ]

35:17.282 --> 35:20.050
The nsa is a powerful weapon
against terror,

35:20.052 --> 35:23.286
And with great power
comes great responsibility.

35:23.288 --> 35:27.324
I am confident that our new nsa
director will wield that power

35:27.326 --> 35:31.328
With wisdom and, when necessary,
with might.

35:31.330 --> 35:33.430
It is with great pleasure
that I introduce

35:33.432 --> 35:36.433
Our newest director of
the national security agency,

35:36.435 --> 35:38.001
Jacob hamilton ballard.

35:38.003 --> 35:39.803
Jake.

35:39.805 --> 35:41.438
[ applause ]

35:41.440 --> 35:43.740
[ camera shutters clicking ]

35:49.148 --> 35:50.780
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

35:50.782 --> 35:52.015
Olivia.

35:52.017 --> 35:53.083
Where is he?

35:58.123 --> 36:01.525
It was you -- wasn't it? --
From the very beginning.

36:01.527 --> 36:03.960
You stole the files.
You called the<i> post.</i>

36:03.962 --> 36:08.131
Billy torrance was just a patsy,
a tool, collateral damage.

36:08.133 --> 36:09.799
He truly loved
diane peters,

36:09.801 --> 36:11.368
And you destroyed them all

36:11.370 --> 36:13.436
So you could force
her resignation

36:13.438 --> 36:15.205
And have yourself
named her successor.

36:15.207 --> 36:17.340
I'm detecting a note of anger
in your voice.

36:17.342 --> 36:20.377
A man is dead, jake --
an innocent man.

36:20.379 --> 36:23.780
Yes, and the world is
a<i> safer</i> place because of it.

36:23.782 --> 36:25.348
How can you say that?

36:25.350 --> 36:27.651
Rowan: Because diane peters
was weak.

36:27.653 --> 36:32.989
She had no idea what was
going on under her nose.

36:32.991 --> 36:35.992
A dragon reared its head,
blew fire from its nostrils,

36:35.994 --> 36:37.794
And all<i> she</i> heard
was thunder.

36:37.796 --> 36:40.230
The world<i> is</i> a safer place,

36:40.232 --> 36:42.632
And you can either stand there
like a 12-year-old

36:42.634 --> 36:44.534
And lecture me about morality
or, even worse,

36:44.536 --> 36:46.803
Rat us out in the name
of justice

36:46.805 --> 36:50.073
Or you can take your cue from us
and get yourself some power --

36:50.075 --> 36:54.477
<i> Real</i> power -- 1600
pennsylvania avenue power.

36:54.479 --> 36:56.546
You<i> think</i> you have that now,

36:56.548 --> 36:58.081
But you're standing
on the sidelines,

36:58.083 --> 36:59.516
Screaming at the referee

36:59.518 --> 37:02.652
Like a sad, drunk parent
at a high-school football game.

37:02.654 --> 37:04.688
If you're okay with that,
by all means.

37:04.690 --> 37:06.823
But I know my daughter
as I know my son,

37:06.825 --> 37:09.893
And I know
<i> that</i> won't suffice.

37:09.895 --> 37:12.295
♪♪

37:20.572 --> 37:22.639
[ cellphone ringing ]

37:26.245 --> 37:29.579
[ sighs ]

37:29.581 --> 37:30.614
[ cellphone beeps ]

37:32.017 --> 37:33.583
Hello, sir?

37:33.585 --> 37:35.185
It's gonna take
some maneuvering

37:35.187 --> 37:36.853
To get the armed services
committee

37:36.855 --> 37:38.855
To confirm captain ballard
as the new director.

37:38.857 --> 37:41.458
Some maneuvering, yes.
Armed services.

37:41.460 --> 37:43.026
Well, if that's all, sir --

37:43.028 --> 37:45.528
I could dennis out to
the golf course at andrews,

37:45.530 --> 37:47.564
But if it's gonna be six hours
of misery,

37:47.566 --> 37:49.366
I'd just as soon
invite him to lunch.

37:49.368 --> 37:51.268
Yeah, I could see the argument
for that.

37:51.270 --> 37:53.036
[ breathes deeply ]
well --

37:53.038 --> 37:55.238
Remind me, I want to talk about
a reorganization at treasury.

37:55.240 --> 37:57.207
And the fourth revised
national climate assessment

37:57.209 --> 37:59.209
Just came out...
-Mr. President.

37:59.211 --> 38:00.494
...And affects some of our
carbon-reduction initiatives.

38:00.495 --> 38:01.778
I don't know if you've had
a chance to read it.

38:01.780 --> 38:04.080
Also, the g8 summit in london,
which I want you to attend.

38:04.082 --> 38:05.982
We're still on for the gridiron
dinner tomorrow night, right?

38:05.984 --> 38:06.716
No.

38:06.718 --> 38:07.917
No?

38:07.919 --> 38:09.319
Hold on.

38:09.321 --> 38:10.487
[ cellphone beeps ]

38:13.592 --> 38:14.924
You hung up on me.

38:14.926 --> 38:16.226
No.

38:16.228 --> 38:18.128
No, you really did.
Ask charlotte.

38:18.130 --> 38:18.995
There was a click.

38:18.997 --> 38:20.463
No.

38:20.465 --> 38:21.464
I<i> haven't</i> read the fourth

38:21.466 --> 38:22.632
Revised national climate
assessment.

38:22.634 --> 38:24.501
I haven't read the third
revised one, either,

38:24.503 --> 38:26.670
Because I am not the head
of the national

38:26.672 --> 38:29.139
Oceanic and atmospheric
administration, sir.

38:29.141 --> 38:32.242
I am also not the secretary
of energy or treasury

38:32.244 --> 38:34.811
Or the director of the united
states geological survey

38:34.813 --> 38:36.246
Or a golfer,
for that matter.

38:36.248 --> 38:37.847
What is your point?

38:37.849 --> 38:39.916
My point is, I am the
white house press secretary

38:39.918 --> 38:42.619
And I love my job and I work
tirelessly at my job.

38:42.621 --> 38:45.155
And I would be happy
to stay here, right here,

38:45.157 --> 38:48.124
24 hours a day, 7 days a week
to do my job

38:48.126 --> 38:50.427
Or to be of help in any way
that was truly productive

38:50.429 --> 38:51.928
For you
and this administration.

38:51.930 --> 38:53.697
But the job I've had
around here recently

38:53.699 --> 38:55.165
Is a different kind of job,

38:55.167 --> 38:58.001
And it seems to amount to no
more than keeping you company.

38:58.003 --> 38:59.936
I'm not a companion animal!

38:59.938 --> 39:01.871
So, respectfully, sir, no,

39:01.873 --> 39:03.606
We're not on
for the gridiron dinner.

39:03.608 --> 39:05.108
And if there's nothing else
right now,

39:05.110 --> 39:06.543
Since I'm already awake
and here,

39:06.545 --> 39:08.278
I think I'll go work
in my office,

39:08.280 --> 39:10.113
Where there is plenty of work
to be done,

39:10.115 --> 39:12.415
And where I'm always available
if you actually need me.

39:19.291 --> 39:22.359
Ha! Well done, red.

39:22.361 --> 39:24.027
Okay, good for you.

39:24.029 --> 39:26.062
Uh-huh.
Good work-wifing, red.

39:26.064 --> 39:28.565
Yeah.

39:28.567 --> 39:29.799
[ sighs ]

39:29.801 --> 39:30.900
Red.

39:30.902 --> 39:33.737
Re-e-e-ed, I'm not
interested anymore.

39:33.739 --> 39:34.804
Say less words.

39:34.806 --> 39:37.240
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

39:37.242 --> 39:39.743
[ indistinct conversation ]

39:39.745 --> 39:41.077
Hey.

39:41.079 --> 39:42.812
