40:42.741 --> 40:44.040
I want to be president.

40:44.042 --> 40:46.276
Which is why you don't write
a book that screams,

40:46.278 --> 40:47.444
"I want to be president."

40:47.446 --> 40:49.479
It's clichéd, insipid,
formulaic, dishonest.

40:49.481 --> 40:50.413
[ scoffs ]
don't hold back.

40:50.415 --> 40:51.748
I am. Believe me.

40:51.750 --> 40:52.782
The only book people want
to read by you

40:52.784 --> 40:54.150
Is a book that talks
about all the things

40:54.152 --> 40:55.485
That aren't actually
in this book.

40:55.487 --> 40:57.454
Don't get me wrong.
You can publish this.

40:57.456 --> 40:59.889
It will sell explosive sales
for exactly one week,

40:59.891 --> 41:01.925
And then the sales
will drop off precipitously

41:01.927 --> 41:04.127
And the books that do sell
will prop open doors

41:04.129 --> 41:06.463
And raise computer monitors
for a generation.

41:06.465 --> 41:09.599
You can publish this
or you can write a real book

41:09.601 --> 41:11.968
That tells the american people
who you are,

41:11.970 --> 41:13.503
What you've been through,

41:13.505 --> 41:16.005
What you think about
what you've been through.

41:16.007 --> 41:17.340
A book that is truthful.

41:17.342 --> 41:19.108
A book that is hard.

41:19.110 --> 41:21.945
This book was easy to write
and easy to forget.

41:21.947 --> 41:24.514
The book you need to write
will be hard,

41:24.516 --> 41:26.416
But people
will remember it.

41:26.418 --> 41:29.319
That book will help
make you president.

41:33.492 --> 41:36.326
I want to write that book.

41:40.599 --> 41:42.499
Well, then
I'll call you tomorrow

41:42.501 --> 41:43.867
And we can get started.

